<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747129>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Male holotype (a–c, g, i, j, k) and female paratype (d–f, h, l, m) of Leptostylum oligothrix Gudin and Messas sp. nov., deposited at MZSP. From Jundiaí, São Paulo, Brazil. (a) Head, male, dorsal view. (b) Head, male, frontal view. (c) Head, male, lateral view. (d) Head, female, dorsal view. (e) Head, female, frontal view. (f) Head, female, lateral view. (g) Dorsal habitus, male. (h) Dorsal habitus, female. (i) Lateral habitus, male. (j) Wing, male, dorsal view. (k) Abdomen, latero-ventral view, showing sex patches on tergites 3, 4 and 5. (l) Lateral habitus, female. (m) Wing, female, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747129/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747133>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Male and female terminalia of Leptostylum oligothrix Gudin and Messas sp. nov. (a) Male terminalia, exhibiting posterior and lateral views, respectively. (b) Female terminalia, exhibiting dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. Scale bar: 1 mm. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; distph, distiphallus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; epand, epandrium; epiph, epiphallus; epiprct, epiproct; hypd, hypandrium; hyprct, hypoproct; pgt, postgonite; phapod, phallapodeme; pregt, pregonite; st, sternite; sur, surstylus; tg, tergite." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747133/files/figure.png" .

